---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Robot Art"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={9}
  phase="Phase 3: Creative Play"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="🎨"
  objective="Use Reachy movements to create a story or artwork"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Your child will use Reachy as a creative tool — combining movements, emotions, and storytelling to create an original "robot performance."
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Pick a Story (5 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Choose a favourite fairy tale or make one up. Identify 5 key moments to act out with Reachy.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Write the Script (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">On paper: write the story in 5 lines. Under each line, note the movement + emotion Reachy should do.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Perform! (15 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Your child narrates while Reachy performs. Switch roles: let Reachy "tell" the story while your child acts it out!</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># robot_story.py — Week 9: Little Explorers
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def perform(self, narration, action, emotion):
        print(f"📖 Narrator: {narration}")
        print(f"🤖 Reachy does: {action}")
        print(f"😊 Reachy feels: {emotion}")
        print()
        time.sleep(2)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()

# Your story here! Change the scenes!
story_scenes = [
    ("Once upon a time, Reachy woke up.", "stretches arms wide", "happy"),
    ("Reachy looked around the room.", "turns head left and right", "curious"),
    ("Suddenly, something fell with a CRASH!", "freezes still", "surprised"),
    ("Reachy bravely went to investigate.", "waves arm forward", "excited"),
    ("Everything was fine. Reachy smiled.", "gentle head nod", "happy"),
]

print("🎭 Robot Story Time!\n")
for narration, action, emotion in story_scenes:
    robot.perform(narration, action, emotion)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "What was the best part of your robot story?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Could Reachy be in a real movie someday?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 This is a capstone for Phase 3 — your child is now programming structured data (tuples in a list) and thinking like a creative director. Celebrate that!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
